Remember that Sender chooses an information policy $p\in\Delta(\mathopen[0,1\mathclose])$ maximizing
\begin{equation*}
\int_{0}^{1}\hat{v}(\mu)\,\mathrm{d}p(\mu),
\end{equation*}
where
\begin{equation*}
\hat{v}(\mu)=\left\{\begin{array}{cc}
1 & \mathrm{if} \quad \mu\geq\tilde{\mu} \\
0 & \mathrm{if} \quad \mu<\tilde{\mu}
\end{array}\right.,
\end{equation*}
for every $\mu\in\Delta(\Omega)$ , subject to the Bayes plausibility constraint
\begin{equation*}
\int_{0}^{1}\mu\,\mathrm{d}p(\mu)=\mu_0.
\end{equation*}
That is , the threshold belief $\tilde{\mu}$ given in \cref{eqn:mutilde} corresponds to the \emph{smallest Bayesian posterior Sender needs to induce to persuade Receiver to take action            } .
