\begin{corollary}  \label{cor:sender_comp_stat_2x2}
Assume $A=\Omega=\{0,1\}$ , $v(a,\omega)=a$ for all $a,\omega\in\{0,1\}$ and $C(\eta,\mu)=\mathrm{D_{KL}}(\eta,\mu)$ for all $\eta,\mu\in\mathopen[0,1\mathclose]$ .
Sender designs weakly less ( Blackwell ) informative optimal policies and achieves a weakly higher payoff when interacting with a wishful Receiver compared to a Bayesian for any prior $\mu_0\in\mathopen]0,1\mathclose[$ if and only if one of the conditions in \cref{prop:comp_stat_2x2} is satisfied .
\end{corollary}
