Accordingly , the initial unemployment gap is larger , and the efficient allocation falls outside of the purple cone .
Hence , monetary policy cannot eliminate the unemployment gap before reaching the ZLB .
The best that monetary policy can do is reduce the nominal interest rate to $0$ , and bring the economy to the ZLB .
There tightness is $\t^z<\t^*$ , so the unemployment gap remains positive . }
